      <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="neighbourhood"></a>Neighbourhood Watch thank Sanderstead Residents Association in their latest newsletter</h3>
      <p>"As a result of the income generated by individuals, co-ordinators, or groups (especially Sanderstead Residents’ Association) we are now in a better financial position. I would like to thank those of you who have made, or promised to make, donations to help ensure the future of the charity..." Read more in the <%= link_to "latest newsletter which can be downloaded here", "http://cbnwa.com/wp/index.php/newsletters/" %>.</p>
      <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="skyscraper"></a>Chris Philp MP urges us to sign a petition and object to plans to build a 17 storey skyscraper in Purley</h3>
      <p>Dear All, Last month, a planning application was submitted to build a 17 floor skyscraper in the centre of Purley on the site with the grey hoardings on Purley Cross.</p>
 
      <p>The owner of the site had wanted to build a much smaller building which included community facilities. However, Croydon Council has made various demands (including a £2m cash payment to the council and a significant social housing component which requires a subsidy) meaning that the only way the scheme is financially viable is to build 17 floors. The council has indicated in Pre-Application hearings that it is minded to approve the planning application for the 17 floor Skyscraper.</p>
 
      <p>I and many other local campaigners (including 7 local residents' associations) believe that a 17 floor skyscraper is totally out of keeping with a peaceful town like Purley, where the next tallest building is only 5 floors. There is a danger that other developers will in the future try to use this as a precedent to build more skyscrapers in Purley. Finally, there are only 37 parking spaces for 220 flats, which will add to the existing parking problems in Purley.</p>
 
      <p>The site does need redeveloping but a much smaller scheme would be more suitable. Full details of the planning application are on the council website under planning reference 16/02994/P.</p>
 
      <p>Please join me in opposing the skyscraper by doing the following:
      <ol>
        <li>Sign my online petition at: <%= link_to "www.surveymonkey.com/r/StopPurleySkyscraper", "https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/StopPurleySkyscraper" %>. Please also forward this link to as many friends and neighbours as you can.</li>
 
        <li>Submit your own objection directly to the council by this Monday (11th July)
Email them at <%= mail_to "development.management@croydon.gov.uk" %> quoting reference 16/02994/P explaining your views on the proposed scheme.</li>
 
       <li>Attend a demonstration on the steps of the Town Hall on Katharine Street in Croydon Town Centre at 6pm on Monday 18th July. This coincides with the start of the next full Council Meeting at which Councillors will be considering the Local Plan, which includes provision for a skyscraper in Purley.</li>
     </ol></p>
 
      <p>Please join me in trying to prevent this totally inappropriate skyscraper.</p>
 
      <p>Kind regards, Chris Philp MP, Member of Parliament for Croydon South</p>

      <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="memorial"></a>Sanderstead Memorial Hall</h3>
      <p>Sanderstead Memorial Hall was built as a tribute to the men and women who died or served their country in the First World War. The hall was opened in June 1922 by Vice Admiral A.F.B. Carpenter VC of Zeebrugge fame. The Sanderstead Hall Association was formed in 1923 to manage the hall. The hall is used as a facility for residents of Sanderstead and, subject to availability and proposed use, may be hired. It is used on a regular basis for various activities by several groups. These include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The Cavat School of Dance</li>
          <li>Castle Day Nursery</li>
          <li>Dog Training Class</li>
          <li>Beeches Badminton Club</li>
        </ul> 
        <p>The hall is managed on a daily basis by Caroline Hubbard and overseen by a small, volunteer committee who meet twice a year to review the management of the hall and any refurbishments necessary. We would like to see a few more volunteers join this small committee and continue the work of this facility in Sanderstead.</p>
        <p>If you are interested and would like to find out more please contact Caroline Hubbard on 07775 680087</p>

      <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="builders"></a>A warning about rogue traders in the neighbourhood </h3>
        <p>We have received the following warning from PCSO Sam Brooks, from the Sanderstead Neighbourhood Policing Team: Trading standards are currently dealing with an increased number of cold calling incidents leading to doorstep crime investigations. Callers are preying on vulnerable residents, who in turn have paid thousands out for home improvement works which are unnecessary or of poor quality. Often the work never takes place at all.</p>
        <p>Please look out for your neighbours and friends. If you receive any leaflets or flyers through your door please make the effort and send the leaflets to Trading standards so that we know who is working where in your borough. Your information could help us to solve a crime and to protect a person at risk of financial abuse.</p>
        <p>Please send any flyers/leaflets to <%= mail_to "trading.standards@croydon.gov.uk" %> or by post to Trading Standards, Zone B 10th Floor Bernard Weatherill House, 8 Mint Walk, Croydon, CR0 1EA. To report a doorstep crime incident call 03454 04 05 06.</p>


      <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="guides"></a>Girl Guiding in Sanderstead</h3>
      <p>There are currently 4 active Brownie units for girls aged 7 – 10 years within the Sanderstead area. We meet on a weekly basis during term time at various churches around the area. Our girls take part in a wide variety activities including art &amp; craft, outdoor fun, a variety of sporting challenges, games nights &amp; everyone’s favourite: nights away with all their Brownie friends.</p>

      <p>There is also wide range of badges they can earn either individually or as a unit. These include such things as, cookery, first aid, crime prevention, fire safety, cyclist, artist, book lover, toymaker, hostess &amp; many more.</p>

      <p>Brownies is just one part worldwide family of girl guiding. Enrolling in Brownies gives girls a world of fun, exciting &amp; challenging opportunities. We currently have several spaces available in a couple of our units.</p>

      <p>We are also looking for adult volunteers to help at our meetings. Volunteering is a fun &amp; rewarding way to help the girls of Sanderstead develop &amp; grow. Our adult volunteers are a fun &amp; friendly team who would warmly welcome anyone wishing to help, you only need be able to spare 3 – 4 hours a week.</p>

      <p>If you would like to join us as a Brownie or adult volunteer, please e-mail your contact details to <%= mail_to "jacquiwheel@lineone.net" %></p>

