      <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="scouts"></a>1st Purley Scouts lend a hand</h3>
      <p><%= image_tag "Purley_cubs.jpg", alt: "Purley Cubs" %></p>
      <p>On Saturday 28 February, 22 cubs and leaders from the 1st Purley Cub Scouts carried out a litter pick covering pockets of private land and footways between Purley Park Road, Brancaster Lane, Lower Barn Road, Mitchley Avenue, Buttermere Gardens, Ingleboro Drive and Honister Heights. They collected 38 bags of litter. The Cubs will now take part in a reflection session at cubs to look at how they felt when they saw the litter and how they felt after the litter was cleared. They will then look at how this will make them act in the future regarding litter. The cubs are working on their "Our World" badge, which asks them to identify an issue in the community and how the pack can help with it.</p>

      <p>Tracy Bellamy, Croydon Council Clean and Green Champion co-ordinator, thanks the 1st Purley Cubs who were polite, well behaved and a credit their pack.</p>

